residence_info.detect_method_en:
1.	Find whether the ofsLogin.jsp file exists in the system, if it does not exist, it will not be affected by this vulnerability, and continue the second step if it exists;
2.	Check out the current version of E-Cology. If it is not version 9, it will not be affected by this vulnerability, if it is version 9, continue the third step;
You can view the e-cology version information through the ecology.ver file
3.	By searching for patch ecology\WEB-INF\myclasses\weaver\security\rules\ruleImp \SecurityRuleOfcLogin.class to see whether a patch exists, if it exists, it is not affected by this vulnerability, and if it does not exist, it may be affected by the vulnerability.
